## Dataset Analysis
The dataset contains approximately 45,000 news articles.

Each sample includes:
- title
- text
- subject
- date
- label (0 = fake, 1 = real)

I analyzed:
- class distribution
- text length
- missing values

The dataset is slightly imbalanced, with more fake news than real news.

---

## Experiments
No machine learning models were trained this week.

The focus was on understanding the dataset and preparing it for further processing.

---

## Problems / Challenges
- Some rows caused parsing errors when loading CSV files
- There were missing values in the text column
- News articles have very different lengths

---

## Solutions
- Used the Python engine in pandas to handle CSV parsing issues
- Skipped malformed rows using `on_bad_lines="skip"`
- Removed missing text values using `dropna()`

